<p>S&amp;P Global Ratings lowered France’s sovereign rating to A+/A-1 from AA-/A-1+, citing heightened uncertainty over public finances amid recent political instability and the government’s suspension of a 2023 pension reform [france24.com#1][politico.eu#1]. The agency maintained a stable outlook but warned that debt dynamics and the pace of fiscal consolidation have weakened without additional measures [politico.eu#1][ft.com#1]. The French government responded that it remains committed to reducing the deficit, with Finance Minister Roland Lescure reaffirming the 2025 objective [lemonde.fr#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/zW2Jmtq2PqDhwEi01a7Vrbc_wjt90iW1Ymj7qzMCwltoDIOFL__TySNYPX868q5nASZ7LHMFOuKyv7Tk5MUijn007eRWV2lEBisePqsFg03hsiYU-EggGQETNVl9Fo61hm5xe-C8Sf7Jsa4Ptp-LnOyxxUY74F7Mb0W7DjZoU7Vo2ec2ZrEDsBEW3uag1w2wgWMmIg' alt='S&amp;P Global’s logo and rating symbols displayed in Toulouse on October 14, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Debt trajectory: S&amp;P expects France’s government debt to reach about 121% of GDP by 2028, compared with 112% at the end of last year [rt.com#1].</li><li>Deficit path: S&amp;P believes the 2025 general government deficit target of 5.4% of GDP will be met, but says consolidation will be slower without extra measures [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Ratings specifics: The cut moved France to A+/A-1 from AA-/A-1+, with a stable outlook, in an unscheduled update late Friday [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Political backdrop: Prime Minister Sébastien Lecornu survived two no-confidence votes on Thursday after freezing the 2023 pension law until the 2027 presidential election, a concession to the Socialist Party [politico.eu#1][rt.com#1].</li><li>Growth outlook: S&amp;P projects 0.7% GDP growth in 2025 and only a muted recovery in 2026, noting risks if higher sovereign borrowing costs spill into the broader economy [politico.eu#1][rt.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>The collective responsibility of the government and parliament - Roland Lescure</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>S&amp;P Global Ratings: Uncertainty on France’s public finances remains elevated and, without additional measures, budget consolidation will likely be slower over the forecast horizon. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/france-downgraded-by-sp-as-budget-uncertainty-remains-elevated/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li><li>French government: Authorities reaffirm their determination to meet the 2025 deficit objective of 5.4% of GDP. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/economy/article/2025/10/18/s-p-cuts-france-credit-rating-from-aa-to-a_6746542_19.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Finance minister Roland Lescure: Called on parliament to pass a budget that puts the deficit on a path toward the EU’s 3% ceiling. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626651-sp-downgrades-frances-credit-rating/'>RT</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/1fe41c81-ac0c-4bc2-b760-4d9a3bb15895'>S&amp;P cuts France’s credit rating as it forecasts higher debt pile</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/business/20251018-s-p-cuts-france-s-credit-rating-to-a-over-political-instability-risking-deficit'>S&amp;P cuts France’s credit rating to A+ over political instability risking deficit</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626651-sp-downgrades-frances-credit-rating/'>S&amp;P downgrades France’s credit rating</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/economy/article/2025/10/18/s-p-cuts-france-credit-rating-from-aa-to-a_6746542_19.html'>S&amp;P cuts France credit rating from AA to A+</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/france-downgraded-by-sp-as-budget-uncertainty-remains-elevated/'>France downgraded by S&amp;P as budget uncertainty ‘remains elevated’</a> - politico.eu</li></ul>